[overseer]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 0;
		screen_text = "Welcome to Aldebaran! I'm excited to see you arrive - The Seeress has never spoken wrong, but the news of Humans coming in peace out of the Lost Worlds was just too remarkable...";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 1;
		screen_text = "You must understand, the last Humans this world has seen were Bandits from a Sirian moon, half a millennium ago.
I'm sure others can tell you more about the history. And if you're really interested, you should seek out the library in the Palace ruins.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 2;
		screen_text = "I am 10th Legion Decurio Eekir, at the service of Her Majesty the Stellar Empress. We are on duty on this little island to protect the ancient ruins of Iliyuna - specifically the Palace of Light and the Interstellar Teleporter. Of course, it is more kind of a guard of honour, since after the last Sirian battle this planet has been practically cut off from the stars - until now...";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 3;
		screen_text = "Unfortunately, we do not possess the Aranna Starstone. The only Starstone we have is that of Sirius, and our wise Empress has decided not to venture thither anymore after the last battle - too great was the risk of releasing the evil breed of this star to the world again. You see, it basically went like this: During the last Sirian battle, the Reptiloids managed to steal all of our Starstones except that one, but we managed to break their side of the Teleporter. Since then both our worlds are stuck in a stalemate, and all we could do is pray for Ashtar to return.
The Seeress says it lies in your fate to re-unite what has dwindled apart, but she could not tell whether under the aegis of Agalla or the Reptiloids. Well, maybe it's time to find out...";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
	[text*]
	{
		complete_quest* = aldebaran_overseer;
		screen_text = "So, if you want to venture to Sirius, listen closely:
First: The Sirius Starstone lies in the room of alchemy in the Palace of Light. You can reach it via the roof.
Second: Our knowledge of what might await you on Sirius is half a millennium old, but here's what we know: The Interstellar Teleporter does not go directly to the main planet like on other worlds. They moved it onto an asteroid, and the teleporter down to the planet of the Reptiloids is guarded by three Darkness Generators located on its three moons - the Bandit Moon, the Moon of Machines, and the Moon of Death. Nomen est Omen.
Third: I will permit you to hire my legionnaires. There is however a certain deposit to be paid as required by law. If you can pay it, talk to them to hire them.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[priestess]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 0;
		screen_text = "Hail Ashtar, o visitor from the Lost Worlds!";
	}
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 1;
		screen_text = "What do you mean, you do not know about our Lord and Savior, Commander Ashtar?
I am confused; are you not from Aranna itself?";
	}
	[text*]
	{
		choice = more;
		order = 2;
		screen_text = "Ashtar Sheran, Commander of the Galactic Fleet of the Warriors of Light! It was Him who kept the Empire of Stars alive and turned it into a force of Good. It was Him, who in the darkest hour of the Empire visited the leaders of the 10th Legion in visions, telling them to stand by the true Emperor Veransk III and not bow down to the evil Utgard (whose name is not spoken here) that usurped the throne. It was Him, Commander Ashtar, who helped the 10th Legion stay victorious against all odds and bring Veransk III safely to Agalla. Hail Ashtar!";
	}
	[text*]
	{
		order = 3;
		screen_text = "To our knowledge, He is still watching over the Lost Worlds that needed His service more than us. But one day He shall return, and open up the way to the stars again for us.
I wish you good luck and Ashtar's blessings for your idea to teleport down to Sirius, but if you ask me, nothing good can come out of it; better to wait upon His return.
Do the people of Aranna at least still know about Azunai the Defender? Well that's something, at least.";
	}
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Hail Ashtar, o visitor from the Lost Worlds!";
	}
}
[seeress]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I saw the arrival of warriors from the Lost Worlds and could hardly believe it myself. The dream came often, but sometimes I saw wayless jungles being settled again, palaces being rebuilt, peoples separated by centuries re-uniting - and sometimes I saw a castle built of tears, standing in clouds made of blood, all watched over by the cold eye of the lizard. Great fate lies in you, no doubt, but be careful with it. And may Azunai defend you, always.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
